syncing state. Before this CL they achieved that by disabling

kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos and invoking signinWithFakeIdentity.

entry.title: Fix google.patch in third_party/hunspell
entry.content:
While working on the bdict parser, I noticed that the patch didn't

apply. Or rather, it did apply but silently threw away some data because

the patch got corrupted at some point! (The header lines have the wrong

line count.)



The problem seems to date to https://crrev.com/c/702640, which

hand-edited the patch but got it wrong. The + and - were backwards

and, by merging two chunks together, the line headers needed to be

updated.



We also forgot to update src/hunspell/utf_info.cxx the last time we

updated hunspell. Upstream reformatted the file and added license

headers.



I've reconciled this by recreating the patch from scratch:



1. Clone hunspell from git at v1.6.0

2. Copy upstream's latest src/hunspell/utf_info.cxx into Chromium

3. Replace hunspell files with what's in the Chromium source tree

4. Recreate the diff to match what Chromium actually has checked in

5. Inspect the diff of the diff to confirm nothing went awry

entry.title: Specify the underlying type for UMALinuxGlibcVersion
entry.content:
enums are weird. They are neither limited to their listed values, but

nor are they plain ints. If an enum is neither `enum class ...` nor

`enum Foo : T`, its "underlying type" is not "fixed". In that case,

although it is typically sized like an int, the range of values is

defined by some bizarre "hypothetical integer type with minimal width"

rule.

https://eel.is/c++draft/dcl.dcl#dcl.enum-8



RecordLinuxGlibcVersion() specifically wants to store the full range of

uint32_t in the enum, so just specify an underlying type of uint32_t.

This fixes one of the two UBSan errors in this (and several other) test

failures:

https://luci-milo.appspot.com/ui/inv/build-8752555092756764593/test-results?q=All%2FAboutFlagsBrowserTest.ExpiryHidesFlag%2F0&sortby=&groupby=

PlusAddressService currently only stores (origin, plus_address) pairs,

ignoring PlusProfile::profile_id. As a result, PlusAddressService::

incompletely initialized PlusProfiles (profile_ids missing).

In case sync integration is disabled, the database is not used and the

profile_ids are not available through the RPC to the backend. In those

cases, the profile_ids remain 0.

When the browser crashes during a kiosk session, the ChromeOS device

to the login screen, from where the kiosk app is launched through

the full launch process.

entry.title: Add mechanism to observe sync bridge from UI sequence
entry.content:
Defines a PlusAddressWebDataService::Observer with an

OnWebDataChangedBySync() event. The observer list is owned by the

PlusAddressWebDataService and only accessed through the UI sequence.



In order for the sync bridge to trigger this notification, a

base::RepeatingClosure is passed in through its constructor. This uses

a combination of WeakPtr + base::BindPostTask() to jump between the

sequences.



The event itself takes a vector, containing the newest set

of data from the database. This avoids round trips back to the database,

when observers want to know what has actually changed.



PlusAddressService is added as an observer. Whenever

OnWebDataChangedBySync() is triggered, it updates its internal cache,

triggering notifications to its own observer in the process.

entry.title: [//media] Simplify MailboxVideoFrameConverter texture target calculation
entry.content:
This CL simplifies the logic of MailboxVideoFrameConverter's calculation

of the texture target to use: it needs to use the external target iff

using external sampling and should use GL_TEXTURE_2D otherwise. In this

case, using external sampling is equivalent to "the buffer format passed

in is multiplanar": the current calculation for this use case always

uses BufferPlane::DEFAULT, which signifies external sampling rather

than per-plane sampling when used with multiplanar textures.



As this logic is the platform-specific and service-side equivalent of

the logic that we are rolling out with

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget(), we put this change under the

same killswitch.



In the long term, this change will be able to be ported to use

ClientSharedImage::GetTextureTarget() directly, as this use case will

itself be ported to use ClientSharedImage. There is a fairly lengthy

road to get there though.

entry.title: [//gpu] Remove usage of GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget()
entry.content:
OzoneImageTexturesHolder invokes GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget().

Instances of this class are created by the OzoneImageBacking when it

produces GL textures [1]. They can thus be created only on ChromeOS and

Linux (the third Ozone platform is Fuchsia, but Fuchsia does not support

GL at all and thus cannot create GL textures for this class to hold).

For ChromeOS and Linux the platform-specific texture target is

GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES [1]. This CL hardcodes that target as part of

removing all usage of GetPlatformSpecificTextureTarget() outside of

ClientSharedImage.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:gpu/command_buffer/service/shared_image/ozone_image_backing.cc;l=344;drc=e9fe61fd0dc3b731e9ee186f9dde74d986e3592d;bpv=1;bpt=1

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:gpu/command_buffer/common/gpu_memory_buffer_support.cc;l=184-186?q=GetPlatformSpecificTextur&ss=chromium

entry.title: Remove LacrosSharedComponentsDir flag and switch
entry.content:
This change removes the LacrosSharedComponentsDir feature's flag and

switch, but maintains its behavior.



While storing Lacros components in a shared directory within

/home/chronos did not directly cause issues, the feature's

enabling switch was not consistently propagated to all processes

(beyond the browser process).



This inconsistency could lead to problems with Widevine, which

must establish its hint file's directory in both the browser and a

utility process.



By ensuring Lacros always uses the shared components directory,

this change eliminates the need to propagate the switch across all

processes.
